  "text": "The Kubernetes API server write chain for Pod creation flows through multiple layers:\n\n1. **REST HTTP Handler** (kubernetes/kubernetes staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/create.go)\n   - The `createHandler` function receives HTTP POST requests for resource creation\n   - It deserializes the request body using negotiated serializers\n   - Calls the REST storage's Create method with the parsed object\n\n2. **Pod REST Storage** (kubernetes/kubernetes pkg/registry/core/pod/storage/storage.go)\n   - The `REST` struct is the concrete REST storage implementation for Pods\n   - Embeds a `genericregistry.Store` which handles the generic CRUD operations\n   - NewStorage() creates and configures this Store with Pod-specific strategies\n\n3. **Generic Registry Store** (kubernetes/kubernetes staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/registry/generic/registry/store.go)\n   - The `Store` struct implements the generic REST storage interface\n   - The Create() method (line 446) validates the object, calls creation strategy hooks\n   - Delegates the actual storage write to `e.Storage.Create()` at line 526\n   - The Storage field is set up in CompleteWithOptions() (line 1620) via the Decorator\n\n4. **etcd3 Store** (kubernetes/kubernetes staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/store.go)\n   - The `store` struct implements the actual etcd3 backend storage (storage.Interface)\n   - Create() method (line 241) encodes the object using the codec at line 260: `runtime.Encode(s.codec, obj)`\n   - Transforms the encoded data at line 275 with encryption/compression via `s.transformer.TransformToStorage()`\n   - Makes the etcd write call at line 283: `s.client.Kubernetes.OptimisticPut()`\n\n5. **Codec Serialization** (kubernetes/kubernetes staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/serializer/codec_factory.go)\n   - The `CodecFactory` creates serializers for JSON, YAML, and Protobuf formats\n   - newSerializersForScheme() creates the appropriate serializers (json.NewSerializer, protobuf.NewSerializer)\n   - These codecs are used by the etcd3 store to encode objects before storing in etcd\n\n6. **etcd Client Kubernetes Wrapper** (etcd-io/etcd client/v3/kubernetes/client.go)\n   - The `Client` struct wraps the etcd client with Kubernetes-specific operations\n   - OptimisticPut() (line 83) creates a transaction with a Compare operation on ModRevision\n   - Uses clientv3.OpPut() to perform the actual put operation within the transaction\n   - Calls Commit() to execute the transaction against etcd\n\n7. **etcd Client KV Interface** (etcd-io/etcd client/v3/kv.go)\n   - The `kv` struct implements the KV interface\n   - Put() method (line 113) delegates to Do()\n   - Do() method (line 144) creates a gRPC request via `kv.remote.Put()` which sends the request to the etcd server"
